quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  53,1,"By the star when it sets:",footnotes:181694:1
  53,2,"your companion has neither strayed nor is he deluded;",footnotes:181695:1,footnotes:181696:2
  53,3,"nor does he speak out of his desire."
  53,4,"This is nothing but a revelation that is conveyed to him,",footnotes:181697:1
  53,5,"something that a very powerful one has imparted to him,",footnotes:181698:1
  53,6,"one endowed with immense wisdom. He came forth and stood poised,",footnotes:181699:1
  53,7,"being on the higher horizon.",footnotes:181700:1
  53,8,"Then he drew near and hung above suspended,"
  53,9,"until he was two bows' length away, or nearer.",footnotes:181701:1
  53,10,"Then he revealed to Allah's servant whatever he had to reveal.",footnotes:181702:1